Instruction: Power down the system and systematically reconfigure the external fast‑connection terminals so that: (1) the power‑supply module’s +12 V output lead is connected to the corresponding +12 V input lead of the control module, and its 0 V output lead is connected to the control module 0 V input; and simultaneously (2) the control module output lead that is at +12 V when the switch is closed is connected to the load module lead that goes to the diode anode (lamp 12 V rail), with the remaining leads forming the 0 V return. In other words, correct BOTH detected polarity inversions by swapping the two plugs at each inter‑module junction until continuity/voltage tests confirm proper orientation.
